<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,294,537]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,366,392]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Comments:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Van Duzee, E. P." box="[344,546,367,393]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 80" refId="ref67052" refString="Van Duzee, E. P. (1904) Annotated list of the Pentatomidae recorded from America, north of Mexico, with descriptions of some new species. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 30 (1), 1 - 80." type="journal article" year="1904">Van Duzee (1904)</bibRefCitation>
first recorded this species from the 
<collectingCountry box="[945,996,367,393]" name="United States of America" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">U.S.</collectingCountry>
, 
<materialsCitation collectorName="Mr. Barber &amp; Mr. Van Duzee" country="United States of America" location="Huachuca Mts." pageId="25" pageNumber="26" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Florida">
indicating that “ 
<collectorName box="[1185,1313,367,393]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Mr. Barber</collectorName>
” had taken a specimen in 
<collectingRegion box="[309,394,403,429]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Florida</collectingRegion>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Barber, H. G." box="[402,561,403,429]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="34 - 39" refId="ref44564" refString="Barber, H. G. (1910) Some Mexican Hemiptera-Heteroptera new to the fauna of the United States. Journal of the New York Entomological Society, 18 (1), 34 - 39." type="journal article" year="1910">Barber (1910)</bibRefCitation>
, however, stated that he had a single specimen, collected in the 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03A9A2761936820AFF6AFEE1FD9EFDDE:8EDF45BB1936820AFB10FE55FA56FE6A" box="[1261,1432,403,429]" country="United States of America" name="Huachuca Mts." pageId="25" pageNumber="26" stateProvince="Florida">Huachuca Mts.</location>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[151,244,439,465]" country="United States of America" name="Arizona" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Arizona</collectingRegion>
, in 1899. Furthermore, he indicated that “this is the specimen which 
<collectorName box="[1009,1177,439,465]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Mr. Van Duzee</collectorName>
determined for me and by mistake recorded from 
<collectingRegion box="[451,532,475,501]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Florida</collectingRegion>
in his ‘List of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[746,898,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Pentatomidae</taxonomicName>
of the United States’”. We do not know of any further published records from the 
<collectingCountry box="[542,592,511,537]" name="United States of America" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">U.S.</collectingCountry>
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
